ObjectStates.Name: Checker_white
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
ALL_MODES = {
    ONE_TO_MANY = 1,
    INDIVIDUAL = 2
}

MODE_BUTTON_INDICES = {
    ONE_TO_MANY = 2,
    INDIVIDUAL = 3
}

MODE_SPECIFIC_INPUT_INDICES = {
    {Var = 8},      --ONE_TO_MANY
    {}              --INDIVIDUAL
}

START_BUTTON_INDEX = 1
DELET_BUTTON_INDEX = 4

ZONE_GUIDS = {
    "a32c17",
    "f67c8c",
    "fac88e",
    "7aafb1",
    "25360d",
    "ff5f1d",
    "cd0a31"
}

active_mode = ALL_MODES.ONE_TO_MANY

local function createModeButtons()
    self.createButton({
      click_function = "activateOneToMany",
      function_owner = self,
      label          = "",
      position       = {2, 1, -23},
      width          = 600,
      height         = 600,
      color          = {1, 1, 1},
      tooltip        = "One to Many:\n Each zone will write the same variable in each script in this zone. The value of the variable can be set individual for each zone."
    })
    self.createButton({
      click_function = "activateIndividual",
      function_owner = self,
      label          = "",
      position       = {2, 1, -21},
      width          = 600,
      height         = 600,
      color          = {1, 1, 1},
      tooltip        = "Individual:\n Each zone will write a individual line of code into each script in this zone."
    })
end

local function createDeleteButton()
    self.createButton({
      click_function = "refreshAllInputs",
      function_owner = self,
      label          = "Refresh",
      position       = {17.5, 1, -4.5},
      width          = 2000,
      height         = 550,
      font_size      = 500,
      font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
      color          = {1, 1, 1},
      tooltip        = "Deletes all user written stuff in each text box."
    })
end

local function createVarInputs()
    if active_mode == ALL_MODES.ONE_TO_MANY then
        for i = 0, 6 do
            self.createInput({
                input_function = "dummy",
                label       = "Value",
                position    = {-21 + (7 * i), 1, -12},
                scale       = {1, 1, 1},
                height      = 550,
                width       = 2000,
                font_size   = 500,
                font_color  = {0, 0, 0},
                color       = {1, 1, 1},
                alignment   = 3,    --Centered
                tab         = 2,    --Select next Input while pressing tab
                tooltip     = "Type in the value of the variable. If the value is a STRING, type in also the quotes!!!"
            })
        end
        self.createInput({
            input_function = "dummy",
            label       = "Name of Variable",
            position    = {0, 1, -15},
            scale       = {1, 1, 1},
            height      = 650,
            width       = 6000,
            font_size   = 600,
            font_color  = {0, 0, 0},
            color       = {1, 1, 1},
            alignment   = 3,    --Centered
            tab         = 2,    --Select next Input while pressing tab
            tooltip     = "Type in the name of the variable you want to create in the scripts of the cards."
        })
    elseif active_mode == ALL_MODES.INDIVIDUAL then
        for i = 0, 6 do
            self.createInput({
                input_function = "dummy",
                label       = "Line",
                position    = {-21 + (7 * i), 1, -20},
                scale       = {1, 1, 1},
                height      = 350,
                width       = 3000,
                font_size   = 300,
                font_color  = {0, 0, 0},
                color       = {1, 1, 1},
                alignment   = 3,    --Centered
                tab         = 2,    --Select next Input while pressing tab
                tooltip     = "Type in the line you want to past into the scripts of the cards."
            })
        end
    end
end

local function createStartButton()
    self.createButton({
      click_function = "startFunction",
      function_owner = self,
      font_size      = 800,
      label          = "INJECT",
      position       = {0, 1, 0},
      width          = 4000,
      height         = 1000,
      color          = {1, 1, 1},
      tooltip        = "Press the button to inject the Lua Code into the scripts of the cards"
    })
end

local function switchMode(newMode)
    for modeName, mode in pairs(ALL_MODES) do
        if mode == newMode then
            for mName, m in pairs(ALL_MODES) do
                self.editButton({index=MODE_BUTTON_INDICES[mName]-1, label="", font_color={0, 0, 0}, font_size=400})
            end
            self.editButton({index=MODE_BUTTON_INDICES[modeName]-1, label="✓", font_color={0, 0, 0}, font_size=400})
            active_mode = mode
            break
        end
    end
end

local function removeExtraInputs()
    if (active_mode == nil) or (MODE_SPECIFIC_INPUT_INDICES[active_mode] == nil) then
        return
    end

    for _, inputIndex in pairs(MODE_SPECIFIC_INPUT_INDICES[active_mode]) do
        self.removeInput(inputIndex - 1)
    end
end

function onLoad(saved_data)
    createStartButton()
    createModeButtons()
    createDeleteButton()
    createVarInputs()

    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        if loaded_data[1] then
            for modeName , mode in pairs(ALL_MODES) do
                if loaded_data[1] == mode then
                    self.editButton({index=MODE_BUTTON_INDICES[modeName]-1, label="✓", font_color={0, 0, 0}, font_size=400})
                    active_mode = mode
                    break
                end
            end
        end
    end
    if active_mode == nil then
        activateOneToMany()
    end
end

function onSave()
    return JSON.encode({active_mode})
end

function activateOneToMany()
    if active_mode == ALL_MODES.ONE_TO_MANY then
        return
    end

    removeExtraInputs()
    local inputs = self.getInputs()
    for i = 1, 7 do
        self.editInput({
            index       = i-1,
            label       = "Value",
            value       = inputs[i].value,
            scale       = {1, 1, 1},
            height      = 550,
            width       = 2000,
            font_size   = 500,
            font_color  = {0, 0, 0},
            color       = {1, 1, 1},
            alignment   = 3,    --Centered
            tab         = 2,    --Select next Input while pressing tab
            tooltip     = "Type in the value of the variable. If the value is a STRING, type in also the quotes!!!"
        })
    end
    self.createInput({
        input_function = "dummy",
        label       = "Name of Variable",
        position    = {0, 1, -15},
        scale       = {1, 1, 1},
        height      = 650,
        width       = 6000,
        font_size   = 600,
        font_color  = {0, 0, 0},
        color       = {1, 1, 1},
        alignment   = 3,    --Centered
        tab         = 2,    --Select next Input while pressing tab
        tooltip     = "Type in the name of the variable you want to create in the scripts of the cards."
    })

    switchMode(ALL_MODES.ONE_TO_MANY)
end

function activateIndividual()
    if active_mode == ALL_MODES.INDIVIDUAL then
        return
    end

    removeExtraInputs()
    local inputs = self.getInputs()
    for i = 1, 7 do
        self.editInput({
            index       = i-1,
            label       = "Line",
            value       = inputs[i].value,
            scale       = {1, 1, 1},
            height      = 350,
            width       = 3000,
            font_size   = 300,
            font_color  = {0, 0, 0},
            color       = {1, 1, 1},
            alignment   = 3,    --Centered
            tab         = 2,    --Select next Input while pressing tab
            tooltip     = "Type in the line you want to past into the scripts of the cards."
        })
    end

    switchMode(ALL_MODES.INDIVIDUAL)
end

function refreshAllInputs()
    local inputs = self.getInputs()
    for _, input in ipairs(inputs) do
        self.editInput({index = input.index, value = ""})
    end
end

local function injectCode(object, zone, zoneIndex)
    local newScript = object.getLuaScript()
    local newLine = ""
    local inputs = self.getInputs()
    if active_mode == ALL_MODES.ONE_TO_MANY then
        local varInput = inputs[MODE_SPECIFIC_INPUT_INDICES[active_mode].Var]
        if varInput.value == "" then
            newLine = newLine .. "newVar"
        else
            newLine = newLine .. varInput.value
        end
        newLine = newLine .. " = "
        print(inputs[zoneIndex].value)
        if inputs[zoneIndex].value == "" then
            return false
        else
            newLine = newLine .. inputs[zoneIndex].value
        end
    elseif active_mode == ALL_MODES.INDIVIDUAL then
        if inputs[zoneIndex] == "" then
            return false
        end
        newLine = newLine .. inputs[zoneIndex]
    else
        printToAll("[fdd835][WARNING][-] No valid injection mode is selected.")
        return false
    end
    newScript = newScript .. [[

    ]] .. newLine .. [[
    ]]
    object.setLuaScript(newScript)
    return true
end

function startFunction()
    local inputs = self.getInputs()
    for zoneIndex, guid in ipairs(ZONE_GUIDS) do
        local zone = getObjectFromGUID(guid)
        local objectsInZone = zone.getObjects()
        for _, zoneObject in pairs(objectsInZone) do
            if inputs[zoneIndex].value ~= "" then
                if zoneObject.getQuantity() > 0 then
                    if zoneObject.name == "Deck" then
                        for _ = 1, zoneObject.getQuantity() do
                            local object = zoneObject.takeObject({position = zoneObject.getPosition():setAt('z', zoneObject.getPosition().z - 5)})
                            injectCode(object, zone, zoneIndex)
                        end
                    else
                        local bagPosition = zoneObject.getPosition():setAt('z', zoneObject.getPosition().z - 5)
                        local bag = spawnObjectJSON({
                            json = [[{
                                    "Name": "Bag",
                                    "Transform": {
                                        "posX": ]] .. bagPosition.x .. [[,
                                        "posY": ]] .. bagPosition.y .. [[,
                                        "posZ": ]] .. bagPosition.z .. [[,
                                        "rotX": 0,
                                        "rotY": 180,
                                        "rotZ": 0,
                                        "scaleX": 1,
                                        "scaleY": 1,
                                        "scaleZ": 1
                                    }
                                }]]})
                        for _ = 1, zoneObject.getQuantity() do
                            local object = zoneObject.takeObject()
                            injectCode(object, zone, zoneIndex)
                            bag.putObject(object)
                        end
                    end
                else
                    injectCode(zoneObject, zone, zoneIndex)
                    zoneObject.setPosition(zoneObject.getPosition():setAt('z', zoneObject.getPosition().z - 5))
                end
            end
        end
    end
end
